properties.otherAdvice:
Large crowds are expected to visit Taronga Zoo during the Summer holiday period between Saturday 27 December and Sunday 4 January. Heavy traffic is expected on roads approaching the Zoo including Military Rd.

Changed traffic conditions will be in place to manage traffic volumes:

  • Stop/slow traffic conditions will be in place between 9am and 3pm on Bradleys Head Rd to manage vehicle access and traffic flow to and from the Zoo car park.
  • When the Zoo car park reaches capacity, road closures will be implemented and there will be no general vehicle access on Bradleys Head Rd from Whiting Beach Rd.
  • Access will be maintained for buses and ferry wharf passengers as well as patrons of the Athol Hall Function Centre and the Sydney Harbour National Park.

Motorists should follow the directions of traffic controllers on site and allow plenty of extra time.

NOTE: road closures and special event clearways will also be in effect on New Year's Eve from 3pm, see details here.
